title: How SpaceX Landed A Rocket... Without Landing Legs. Catching a Giant Rocket With Giant Chopsticks
tags: [none]
description: This morning SpaceX performed the 5th flight of their Starship/SuperHeavy launch system and once again made a clear step forward as they demonstrated precision touchdown with both the booster and the Starship. The booster touchdown demonstrated a radical new recovery method with the rocket carefully maneuvering next to a tower to be caught by a pair of arms, eliminating complicated articulating legs and shock absorbers.The Starship stage flew to the Indian ocean and guided itself to a precision touchdown next to a buoy with a camera, delivering video of the landing and showing the accuracy of the guidance. Even more impressive when it became clear how much damage the control surfaces sustained during entry.Follow me on Twitter for more updates:https://twitter.com/DJSnMI have a discord server where I regularly turn up:https://discord.gg/zStmKbMIf you really like what I do you can support me directly through Patreonhttps://www.patreon.com/scottmanley

description: It's finally here: Elon Musk has revealed his long-awaited autonomous Tesla Robotaxi ‚Äì also referred to as the Cybercab ‚Äì at an event in Los Angeles, USA.Looking a lot like the VW XL1 (remember that?) the Robotaxi has no steering wheel or pedals and just two seats. As the name suggests, its crisp flat surfaces and full-width light bars have more than a passing resemblance to the Cybertruck, too.This, then, is Musk's vision of a grand autonomous future, and he promises the Robotaxi will be in full production by 2026, with prices starting from $30,000.A fleet of 20 fully functioning prototypes were built to run around the Warner Bros. Studio lot ‚Äì the venue for Musk‚Äôs big reveal ‚Äì and take passengers on short, obstacle-laden routes. Top Gear duly hailed one, so join our Editor-in-Chief, Jack Rix, for a first ride in the new Tesla Robotaxi‚Ä¶Subscribe to Top Gear for more videos: http://bit.ly/SubscribeToTopGearWANT MORE TOP GEAR?Listen to the Top Gear Magazine Podcast: https://topgear.podlink.to/PodcastSign up for our newsletter: https://www.topgear.com/newsletter-signup00:00 Intro03:20 Robotaxi04:55 Robotaxi Ride08:12 Walkaround10:36 Chat with Chief Designer 13:30 Tesla Bot15:12 Chat with Marques Brownlee24:22 ConclusionMORE ABOUT TOP GEAR:Welcome to the official home of Top Gear on YouTube. title: The Mar√≠as: Tiny Desk Concert
tags: NPR|NPR Music|National Public Radio|Live|Performance|tiny desk|tiny desk concert|tony desk|tiny concert
description: This Sept. 15 to Oct. 15, NPR Music celebrates artists from all corners of Latinidad with an 'El Tiny' takeover.Anamaria Sayre | October 9, 2024Fresh off the release of its latest album Submarine, The Mar√≠as have never felt more ready-made for the Tiny Desk. With the first few chimes of the synth and notes from Maria Zardoya‚Äôs breathy vocals, the band makes it clear that there‚Äôs no better place to bring its bedroom pop style than this slightly bigger space.The indie band has been skyrocketing over the last few years with classic Spanglish hits like ‚ÄúCari√±o‚Äù (featured here at the Desk) and a collab on Bad Bunny‚Äôs Un Verano Sin Ti. But there‚Äôs so much more to the group than the smooth electronic beats and guitar riffs that meet the ear.Headed by Puerto Rican lead singer Maria Zardoya, who proudly places a Puerto Rican flag on the Desk halfway through the show, there is an authenticity to the group‚Äôs lyricism and presentation that pulses just beneath the emotive keys. The band‚Äôs performance feels like a soundtrack for a generation that exists in many worlds, and in The Mar√≠as Tiny Desk viewers find a new, ethereal, welcoming world to belong to.SET LIST‚ÄúReal Life‚Äù‚ÄúOnly in My Dreams‚Äù‚ÄúNo One Noticed‚Äù‚ÄúCari√±o‚ÄùMUSICIANSMar√≠a Zardoya: vocalsJosh Conway: drumsEddie Friedlander: keysJesse Perlman: guitarGabriel Steiner: keys, percussionDoron Zounes: bassTINY DESK TEAMProducer: Anamaria SayreDirector/Editor: Maia SternAudio Technical Director: Josh NewellHost/Series Producer: Bobby CarterVideographers: Maia Stern, Joshua Bryant, Kara Frame, Mitra I. description: Life has been a little rough around here for the last 3 weeks.
